<subSubSection id="B410B983E0AB5BA3AEC6F0707EBA5486" lastPageId="369" lastPageNumber="370" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="A2372744AC35C0E7CA540FFA66165F9D" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">
<taxonomicName id="03C472FEAC9D9987EBD826BFCDA1363E" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrosum">Bembidium petrosum</taxonomicName>
Gebler, 1833: 275. Type locality: western Siberia (inferred from title of the paper); &quot;Smjeinogorsk, S[outh of] Barnaul, Ob R[iver], Siberia, Russia&quot; selected by Lindroth (1963b: 332). Lectotype (♂), designated by Lindroth (1963b: 332), in ZMH.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06B6E27D49081B4C89AD4B7D3B85D701" lastPageId="369" lastPageNumber="370" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">
<taxonomicName id="58D24177D53F7F160A1A6231925EE4F9" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ochthedromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substrictus">Ochthedromus substrictus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1848: 465. Type locality: &quot;Lacum Superiorem&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) in MCZ [# 5515]. Synonymy established, under 
<pageBreakToken id="689A1B8F816E9EAF196A428F50F1092F" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" start="start">the</pageBreakToken>
name 
<taxonomicName id="4EA7F23BEDC746EB431210E88EC098FA" baseAuthorityName="Faldermann" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidum">
<emphasis id="0467CBBE7900712ADEACEA01194E868B" italics="true" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">Bembidion lucidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LeConte), by LeConte (1863b: 14), confirmed by Lindroth (1954b: 126).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A5C391E72EFEFC2305405EE6420D5BC" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="B7614F593992269D22A065A9467CC817" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ochthedromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidus">Ochthedromus lucidus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1848: 466 [secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="8E89E13D7A01D77086AF3FAC62B834DC" baseAuthorityName="Faldermann" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidum">
<emphasis id="3219A8C176DBB7BBAAEA1FF72A2D72E9" italics="true" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">Bembidion lucidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Faldermann, 1835)]. Type locality: &quot;Lacum Superiorem&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) in MCZ [# 5514]. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1953b: 176).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="72F99856BEA108DFC2831494D82ECA27" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="CAA939CC9633C535F4EBB2DC9ED8CC1D" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1859" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Peryphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subinflatus">Peryphus subinflatus</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1859a: 126. Type locality: &quot;colonie Ross [farming community about 75 miles north of San Francisco along the coast, California]&quot; (original citation). Lectotype, designated by Bousquet and Larochelle (1993: 16), in ZMMU. Synonymy established by Bousquet and Larochelle (1993: 16).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05346EDBD998CD4BFF69365D305D1C0B" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="3BA0E34F7213B0CBEBC3DB6D87C41C0F" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagneri">Bembidium wagneri</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="070B5653BABA322DA177D2CA90220E87" originalValue="Tschitschérine">Tschitscherine</normalizedToken>
, 1893: 377. Type locality: &quot;Krasnojarsk [Siberia, Russia]&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) [3 originally cited] in ZILR. Synonymy established by Netolitzky (1934: 73).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E04CA0AB6F1B9F206BCECA1E6BF075F7" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="532C80ECCCD807E53A64641646797549" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="distinguendum" subSpecies="siebkei">Bembidion distinguendum siebkei</taxonomicName>
J. 
<normalizedToken id="48A11C25249FF2AE42BECE93EE804FBF" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
, 1918: 94. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="D7D5FC1434D2168A914C2242B58DD22E" originalValue="«Scandinavien»">&quot;Scandinavien&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation), restricted to &quot;Mo[e]n [Troms County], R[iver] 
<normalizedToken id="63DD3001D999FAAE1C8738B69302CBEE" originalValue="Målselv">Malselv</normalizedToken>
, N[orthern] Norway&quot; by Lindroth (1963b: 333). Syntype(s) in ZMUT (Lindroth 1963b: 333). Synonymy established by Munster (1921: 60), confirmed by Lindroth (1963b: 333). Note. This name is credited to Sparre Schneider (1910: 72) by several authors (e.g., Lorenz 2005: 232; Marggi et al. 2003: 262; Kryzhanovskij et al. 1995: 86). The 
<normalizedToken id="E1BCBCE5B89F4367044C812757C197AB" originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
name is included and discussed by Sparre Schneider (1910: 72) but no character states are mentioned that would make the name available (see also Netolitzky 1934: 73).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B00121B20543E9921C45006FFF05A707" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="70864FDD042EEE9C87F7443C758186D5" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepusculus">Bembidion lepusculus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 75. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="B20B4109D9E1AB9AC3916FE635378811" originalValue="«Colorado»">&quot;Colorado&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation). Holotype [by monotypy] (♂) in USNM [# 36937]. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1954b: 125).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="08C31ADF1CBDA2470C04B1B35FE47E89" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="77F29E5B2CFE17DA631C9B0B824D6255" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castalium">Bembidion castalium</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 75. Type locality: &quot;Las Vegas [San Miguel County], New Mexico&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♀), designated by Lindroth (1975: 119), in USNM [# 36940]. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1954b: 126).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4AF17C732C45805C5E8619072B3E10F" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="BF5F0D3632DDC99472B5CC885B751541" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1924" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguiceps">Bembidion exiguiceps</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1924: 34. Type locality: &quot;Terrace, British Columbia&quot; (original citation). Lectotype (♀), designated by Lindroth (1975: 119), in USNM [# 36942]. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1954b: 128).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="920921767A4793C293354EDA7A828112" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="9905B128EF1BA9DCA0EB459B6CDC442E" authorityName="Hatch" authorityYear="1950" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wenatchee">Bembidion wenatchee</taxonomicName>
Hatch, 1950: 101. Type locality: &quot;Wenatchee [Chelan County], Washington&quot; (original citation). Holotype (♀) in USNM. Synonymy established by Hatch (1953: 90), confirmed by Lindroth (1954b: 130).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C417B825D26C8F3292694F3B0C2482B" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
<taxonomicName id="050768DA688031C8597C8C012AB47535" authorityName="Kangas" authorityYear="1980" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="petrosum" subSpecies="carlhlindrothi">Bembidion petrosum carlhlindrothi</taxonomicName>
Kangas, 1980: 364. Type locality: &quot;Osnatsennaja, am Jenissej, Sibirien&quot; (original citation). Holotype (♂) in ZMH. Synonymy established by Lindroth (1985: 195).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7875F83F169E52470E3AA39FE41EBDDD" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="531EFC9AAC9FE32834477F41AC6CF667" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E80193AF7D5379E30489249BFB9F8F5" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">
This Holarctic subspecies is known from Scandinavia to eastern Siberia (Marggiet al. 2003: 262) and from Alaska (Lindroth 1963b: 334) to Newfoundland (Lindroth 1955a: 60-61), south to &quot;Rhode Island&quot; (Sikes 2003: 7), southwestern Pennsylvania (Allegheny County, CMNH), 
<normalizedToken id="56E4E2800FBF214F325D1049F4088C7E" originalValue="“Nebraska”">&quot;Nebraska&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Hayward 1897: 81, as 
<taxonomicName id="F78170DC2788BA6B645213BF9BCDE880" baseAuthorityName="Faldermann" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidum">
<emphasis id="BD44DCC6F3D69E13A52AEF86187D8D59" italics="true" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">Bembidion lucidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), northeastern New Mexico (Casey, 1918: 75, as 
<taxonomicName id="0AF1FA42EDE3E555C9230F65F8B00150" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castalium">
<emphasis id="446193F300F5B34A8A11EF7AE21F5CBC" italics="true" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">Bembidion castalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), southern Arizona (Wickham 1898: 300, as 
<taxonomicName id="93375C50DD739C3D45AB24D105409D19" baseAuthorityName="Faldermann" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="369" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucidum">
<emphasis id="57FE41B9ED7B9069B057860D19E0AD15" italics="true" pageId="369" pageNumber="370">Bembidion lucidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and southeastern California (San Bernardino County, MCZ).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
